    "GenAI, in particular, has the potential to support productive student discussions, provide personalized learning experiences, and encourage creativity across different domains [13]; [14].",
    "However, the capacity of GenAI to obscure the distinction between original and AI-generated content raises ethical issues, requiring careful consideration of its educational use [15].",
    "The potential of AI to augment human intelligence opens up unparalleled opportunities for educational research and application [16], yet caution is necessary to ensure AI's sustainable integration into educational practices [17].ChatGPT, a product of OpenAI, exemplifies the capabilities and controversies of GenAI in education.",
    "Offering personalized tutoring, content creation, and active learning engagement, ChatGPT showcases the versatility of conversational AI.",
